s of selected commons in a variety of diagnostic sites where they exist, the ways in which they are being transformed by the incursions of capital and state, and the ways in which they are becoming the locus of struggle for those who depend on them to survive.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCommons. 0aEnvironmental protectionxInternational cooperation. 0aGlobal commons. 0aHuman ecology. 0aNatural resources, CommunalxManagement. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh1 aBoyer, Jefferson C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCunningham, Hilary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLu, Flora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNonini, Donald M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNonini, Donald M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPickles, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScharper, Stephen B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith-Nonini, Sandy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178238480940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782384809423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782384809/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK